  "name": "Blindsight",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/feats/blinding-critical.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Using nonvisual senses, such as sensitivity to vibrations, keen smell, acute hearing, or echolocation, a creature with blindsight can maneuver and fight as well as a sighted creature. <a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf1.conditions\" data-id=\"L3hNCX9kLGlmoQhc\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Invisibility</span></a>, darkness, and most kinds of @Compendium[pf-content.pf-buffs.suDHnshpVR3PXIRG]{Concealment}&nbsp;are irrelevant, though a creature with blindsight must have line of effect to an object or another creature to discern that object or creature.</p>\n<p>The ability&rsquo;s range is specified in the creature&rsquo;s descriptive text. The creature usually does not need to succeed at <a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf1.skills\" data-id=\"YYmmxDgp0g3ltSUG\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Perception</span></a> checks to notice creatures within range of its blindsight ability. Unless noted otherwise, blindsight is continuous, and the creature doesn&rsquo;t need to do anything to use it. Some forms of blindsight, however, must be triggered as a free action. If so, this is noted in the creature&rsquo;s description. If a creature must trigger its blindsight ability, it gains the benefits of blindsight only during its turn.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Format</em>: blindsight 60 ft.</p>\n<p><em>Location</em>: Senses.</p>",
